# Cloudflare Workers/Pages: rewrite unknown paths to the prerendered 404 page.
#
# Static prerendered routes (/, /impressum, /datenschutz, /bav-rechner,
# /etf-vs-bav, /riester-rechner, /altersvorsorgedepot-rechner,
# /riester-vs-altersvorsorgedepot, /basisrente-rechner,
# /private-rentenversicherung-rechner, /rente-netto-berechnen,
# /altersvorsorgeprodukte-vergleichen, /rentenluecke-rechner) take precedence
# over _redirects, so this catch-all only fires for genuinely-unknown URLs.
#
# Status 200 (rewrite) is used because Cloudflare Workers validates _redirects
# and rejects 404 as a redirect target (valid codes: 200, 301, 302, 303, 307,
# 308). The /404.html asset is served directly by the static-asset binding for
# requests to that exact path, so the catch-all below cannot loop.
# dist/404.html is prerendered with noindex,follow so the 200 wire status
# does not affect SEO.
#
# Live verification: `curl -sI https://rentenwiki.de/<unknown-url>` must show
# HTTP/1.1 200 and the 404 page body after deploy.
/*  /404.html  200
